Layer Specifications
Presentation Layer (UI)
Contains: Composables, Fragments, Activities, Adapters, Custom Views, Navigation events

Responsibilities — exactly these, nothing more:

Render the current UiState emitted by the ViewModel
Forward user interactions to the ViewModel as UiEvents
Observe and handle one-shot UiEffect events (navigation, snackbar, dialog)
Manage UI-only state (scroll position, keyboard visibility, animation state)
Hard rules:

✗  Never call Retrofit, Room, DataStore, or any data API directly
✗  Never run business logic or make decisions based on data content
✗  Never launch coroutines with anything other than lifecycleScope
✗  Never collect Flows outside a lifecycle-aware scope
✗  Never manipulate raw data — only render what ViewModel provides
✗  Never use LiveData in new code (StateFlow only)
✗  Never use Kotlin Synthetics (ViewBinding or Compose only)
✓  Composables are stateless — all state comes from ViewModel
✓  Every screen handles all four base states: Loading, Success, Empty, Error
✓  Accessibility: every interactive element has a contentDescription
✓  Every screen supports dark mode, large fonts, and landscape orientation

UI State consumption pattern (Compose):

Screen state is collected with:
  val uiState by viewModel.uiState.collectAsStateWithLifecycle()
One-shot effects consumed with:
  LaunchedEffect(Unit) {
      viewModel.uiEffect.collect { effect ->
          when (effect) {
              is UiEffect.NavigateTo → navController.navigate(effect.route)
              is UiEffect.ShowSnackbar → snackbarHostState.showSnackbar(effect.message)
          }
      }
  }

UI State consumption pattern (Fragment/XML):

State collected with:
  viewLifecycleOwner.lifecycleScope.launch {
      viewLifecycleOwner.repeatOnLifecycle(Lifecycle.State.STARTED) {
          viewModel.uiState.collect { state → render(state) }
      }
  }

ViewModel Layer
Responsibilities — exactly these, nothing more:

Receive UiEvent from UI
Delegate business operations to UseCase classes
Transform results into UiState and emit via StateFlow
Emit one-shot UiEffect via Channel (navigation, snackbar, toast, dialog)
Manage loading, error, retry, and pagination state
Survive configuration changes
Hard rules:

✗  Never import Retrofit, OkHttp, Gson, Room, or any framework-specific data API
✗  Never expose MutableStateFlow or MutableSharedFlow publicly
✗  Never call repository directly — always through a UseCase
✗  Never use GlobalScope or runBlocking
✗  Never perform I/O on the Main dispatcher
✓  Every coroutine launched inside viewModelScope
✓  UiState is a sealed interface with distinct subtypes
✓  Loading, Success, Empty, and Error are always defined
✓  Errors are mapped to human-readable UiState — never raw exceptions exposed

ViewModel structure template:

class [Feature]ViewModel @Inject constructor(
    private val [action]UseCase: [Action]UseCase,
    private val [action2]UseCase: [Action2]UseCase
) : ViewModel() {
    private val _uiState = MutableStateFlow<[Feature]UiState>([Feature]UiState.Loading)
    val uiState: StateFlow<[Feature]UiState> = _uiState.asStateFlow()
    private val _uiEffect = Channel<[Feature]UiEffect>(Channel.BUFFERED)
    val uiEffect: Flow<[Feature]UiEffect> = _uiEffect.receiveAsFlow()
    fun onEvent(event: [Feature]UiEvent) {
        when (event) {
            is [Feature]UiEvent.[Action] → handle[Action](event)
        }
    }
    private fun handle[Action](event: [Feature]UiEvent.[Action]) {
        viewModelScope.launch {
            _uiState.value = [Feature]UiState.Loading
            [action]UseCase(event.param)
                .onSuccess { data →
                    _uiState.value = if (data.isEmpty())
                        [Feature]UiState.Empty
                    else
                        [Feature]UiState.Success(data)
                }
                .onFailure { error →
                    _uiState.value = [Feature]UiState.Error(
                        message = error.toUserMessage(),
                        retryAction = { handle[Action](event) }
                    )
                }
        }
    }
}

