Dependency Injection (Hilt)
Framework: Hilt — always. No manual DI. No Koin unless project already uses it.

Rules:

✗  Never instantiate a dependency with constructor call at the call site
✗  Never use field injection except where Android mandates it (Activity, Fragment,
   BroadcastReceiver, ContentProvider — @AndroidEntryPoint required)
✗  Never use @Singleton for objects with mutable state shared across scopes
✓  Prefer constructor injection for all non-Android classes
✓  Use @Binds to bind interface → implementation (zero runtime cost)
✓  Use @Provides only when you don't own the class (Retrofit, OkHttp, Room)
✓  Scope to the smallest viable scope: @Singleton → @ActivityRetainedScoped → @ViewModelScoped

Hilt module template:

@Module
@InstallIn(SingletonComponent::class)
abstract class [Domain]Module {
    @Binds
    @Singleton
    abstract fun bind[Domain]Repository(
        impl: [Domain]RepositoryImpl
    ): [Domain]Repository
}
@Module
@InstallIn(SingletonComponent::class)
object NetworkModule {
    @Provides
    @Singleton
    fun provideOkHttpClient(): OkHttpClient = OkHttpClient.Builder()
        .connectTimeout(30, TimeUnit.SECONDS)
        .readTimeout(30, TimeUnit.SECONDS)
        .addInterceptor(AuthInterceptor())
        .apply { if (BuildConfig.DEBUG) addInterceptor(HttpLoggingInterceptor()) }
        .build()
    @Provides
    @Singleton
    fun provideRetrofit(client: OkHttpClient): Retrofit = Retrofit.Builder()
        .baseUrl(BuildConfig.BASE_URL)
        .client(client)
        .addConverterFactory(Json.asConverterFactory("application/json".toMediaType()))
        .build()
}

Coroutines & Flow Standards
Dispatcher Assignment (mandatory)
Work Type	Dispatcher	Examples
Network calls	Dispatchers.IO	Retrofit, file download
Database reads/writes	Dispatchers.IO	Room, DataStore
CPU-intensive work	Dispatchers.Default	Audio processing, image resize, JSON parse
UI updates	Dispatchers.Main.immediate	StateFlow emission from ViewModel
The Repository sets the dispatcher. The ViewModel never specifies one.

✗  viewModelScope.launch(Dispatchers.IO) { ... }   ← Wrong: ViewModel sets dispatcher
✓  In Repository/DataSource: withContext(Dispatchers.IO) { ... }
✓  In UseCase: operators are suspend, caller provides scope

Flow Rules
✗  Never use flow { ... } and then collect inside the same class
✗  Never collect Flow inside an Adapter
✗  Never collect Flow inside a Repository — transform it instead
✗  Never use GlobalScope
✗  Never use runBlocking in production code
✓  Repository methods that stream data return Flow<Result<T>>
✓  Flow is always collected inside lifecycleScope.launch { repeatOnLifecycle(STARTED) }
✓  Use .catch { } at the call site to prevent uncaught exceptions
✓  Use .stateIn(viewModelScope, SharingStarted.WhileSubscribed(5000), initialValue)
   to convert upstream Flow to StateFlow in ViewModel

Structured Concurrency
✓  Every coroutine is a child of a well-defined scope (viewModelScope, lifecycleScope)
✓  Cancellation is propagated automatically through parent-child relationships
✓  SupervisorJob is used only at scope level (Hilt-provided scopes), never inline
✓  Use async/await for parallel independent operations
✓  Use coroutineScope { } to create structured sub-scopes inside suspend functions

Result Wrapper (mandatory for all business operations)
// Repository returns kotlin.Result<T>
suspend fun save(model: DomainModel): Result<Long> = runCatching {
    localDataSource.insert(mapper.toEntity(model))
}
// UseCase propagates or transforms
suspend operator fun invoke(param: Param): Result<DomainModel> =
    repository.fetch(param).map { dto → mapper.toDomain(dto) }
// ViewModel maps to UiState
result
    .onSuccess { data → _uiState.value = UiState.Success(data) }
    .onFailure { error → _uiState.value = UiState.Error(error.toUserMessage()) }

✗  Never return null to signal failure
✗  Never throw exceptions across layer boundaries
✗  Never catch Exception at the top level and log without acting
✓  Every failure has a typed error message surfaced to UiState
✓  Every network/IO error produces a retry-capable UiState

