Error Handling Standards
The principle: Errors are data. Every layer transforms errors into the type its consumer expects. Raw exceptions never cross a layer boundary.

Error Propagation Chain
External System (throws IOException, HttpException, SQLiteException)
    ↓
DataSource (catches all, wraps in Result.failure with typed AppError)
    ↓
Repository (propagates Result or maps to domain-level error)
    ↓
UseCase (applies business rules, may transform or re-wrap)
    ↓
ViewModel (maps error to UiState.Error with user-friendly message)
    ↓
UI (renders error state with message + optional retry button)

AppError Hierarchy
sealed class AppError(message: String, cause: Throwable? = null) : Exception(message, cause) {
    // Network errors
    class NoInternet(cause: Throwable? = null) : AppError("No internet connection", cause)
    class Timeout(cause: Throwable? = null) : AppError("Request timed out", cause)
    class ServerError(val code: Int, cause: Throwable? = null) : AppError("Server error ($code)", cause)
    class Unauthorized(cause: Throwable? = null) : AppError("Session expired", cause)
    // Local errors
    class DatabaseError(cause: Throwable? = null) : AppError("Storage error", cause)
    class FileNotFound(val path: String) : AppError("File not found: $path")
    class InsufficientStorage : AppError("Not enough storage space")
    // Business rule violations
    class ValidationError(val field: String, message: String) : AppError(message)
    class OperationNotPermitted(message: String) : AppError(message)
}

HTTP Error Mapping
HTTP Code → AppError
─────────────────────────────────────────────
400        → AppError.ValidationError (parse response body for field errors)
401        → AppError.Unauthorized (trigger token refresh → retry once → logout)
403        → AppError.OperationNotPermitted
404        → Result.success(null) or AppError.FileNotFound (context-dependent)
429        → Retry with exponential backoff + jitter (max 3 retries)
500–503    → AppError.ServerError(code)
IOException → AppError.NoInternet
SocketTimeoutException → AppError.Timeout

User-Facing Error Messages
Extension on Throwable:
fun Throwable.toUserMessage(): String = when (this) {
    is AppError.NoInternet → "Check your internet connection and try again."
    is AppError.Timeout → "The request took too long. Please try again."
    is AppError.ServerError → "Something went wrong on our end. Try again later."
    is AppError.Unauthorized → "Your session has expired. Please sign in again."
    is AppError.InsufficientStorage → "Not enough storage. Free up space and try again."
    is AppError.ValidationError → this.message ?: "Please check your input."
    else → "An unexpected error occurred. Please try again."
}

State Management Deep Dive
StateFlow vs SharedFlow vs Channel
Mechanism	Use For	Key Property
StateFlow	Current UI state	Always has a value; new collectors get current state
SharedFlow	Broadcast events (multiple consumers)	Configurable replay; all active collectors receive
Channel (as Flow)	One-shot UI effects	Single consumer; safe for navigation/snackbar
